"title": "8468: renunciation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8468",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The deliberate rejection or disavowal, especially of a person or object.</p>\n<h2>Renunciation of the LORD</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:12\">JDG 2:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:28\">ISA 1:28</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:8\">EXO 32:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:16\">JOS 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:17\">2KI 22:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:19\">JER 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:10\">MAT 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:12\">2TI 2:12</a></p>\n<h2>Renunciation of evil</h2>\n<h3>In repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:27\">PSA 37:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer35:15\">JER 35:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:6\">EZK 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:27\">DAN 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20\">1TI 6:20</a></p>\n<h3>To find God's mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:14\">2CH 7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:13\">PRO 28:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:21\">EZK 18:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:10\">JON 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Self-renunciation and the Christian life</h2>\n<h3>An integral part of discipleship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:28\">MRK 10:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:28\">LUK 5:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:33\">LUK 14:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8\">PHP 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>The example of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17\">JHN 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:7-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:7–2:8</a></p>",
